<div class="container">
    <h1>Building Steps for a Web App</h1>
    <p>Here are the steps to create a simple web application using <strong>Microsoft Visual Studio</strong>. Follow them in order to set up your project, add code, and run the app.</p>

    <h2>Steps</h2>
    <ol>
        <li><strong>Open Visual Studio</strong><br />Launch Microsoft Visual Studio from your computer.</li>
        <li><strong>Create a new project</strong><br />Go to <code>File → New → Project</code>, then choose <code>ASP.NET Core Web App (Model-View-Controller)</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Configure the project</strong><br />Enter a project name, location, and solution name, then click <em>Create</em>.</li>
        <li><strong>Select framework</strong><br />Pick the latest <code>.NET</code> version, then press <em>Create</em>.</li>
        <li><strong>Explore project structure</strong><br />Notice the folders: <code>Controllers</code>, <code>Views</code>, <code>Models</code>, and <code>wwwroot</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Add a Controller</strong><br />Right-click the <code>Controllers</code> folder → <em>Add</em> → <em>Controller</em>. Choose <code>MVC Controller – Empty</code>, name it <code>HomeController</code>.</li>
        <li><strong>Add a View</strong><br />Right-click the <code>Views</code> folder → <em>Add</em> → <em>New Folder</em> → name it <code>Home</code>. Inside, add a new <code>View</code> (e.g., <code>Index.cshtml</code>).</li>
        <li><strong>Write your code</strong><br />In <code>HomeController.cs</code>, return the <code>Index</code> view. In <code>Index.cshtml</code>, add some HTML to display content.</li>
        <li><strong>Run the application</strong><br />Click the green <em>Run</em> button (IIS Express). The browser will open your web app.</li>
    </ol>

